(d) The 4-velocity of the ZAMO is$$\mathbf {u} = \mathbf {e}_{\hat {\mathbf {t}}} = \left| \mathbf {g}_{\mathbf {tt}} - \omega^{2} \mathbf {g}_{\phi \phi}ight|^{-  rac {1}{2}} \left(\mathbf {e}_{\mathbf {t}} + \omega \mathbf {e}_{\phi}ight).$$The vectors $\mathbf{e}_t$ and $\mathbf{e}_{\phi}$ are Killing vectors. The vector field $\mathbf{e}_t + \omega \mathbf{e}_{\phi}$ is not a Killing vector because $\omega$ is not constant. However any particular ZAMO is moving along the Killing vector $\pmb{\xi} = \mathbf{e}_t + \omega_0\mathbf{e}_{\phi}$ ( $\omega_0$ a fixed constant, which is chosen to equal $\omega$ at the radius of the particular ZAMO under consideration). Thus the results of Problem 10.14 apply and we get$$\mathbf {a} =  rac {1}{2} 
abla \log | \pmb {\xi} \cdot \pmb {\xi} | =  rac {1}{2} 
abla \log | \mathbf {g}_{tt} + 2 \omega_{0} \mathbf {g}_{t \phi} + \omega_{0}^{2} \mathbf {g}_{\phi \phi} |.$$When we set $\mathbf{g}_{t\phi} = -\omega \mathbf{g}_{\phi \phi}$ and evaluate at $\omega = \omega_0$ this becomes$$\mathbf {a} =  rac {1}{2} 
abla \log \left| \mathbf {g}_{\mathrm {tt}} - \omega^{2} \mathbf {g}_{\phi \phi}ight|.$$
